The paper is primarily concerned with designing robotic assistance devices for manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also focuses on improving the usability of semi-autonomous robots, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of computer vision techniques to generate candidate grasps and reach-to-grasp trajectories in novel scenes suggests that the paper may also fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of a feedback controller to facilitate motion towards the most promising grasp suggests that the paper may also fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
